  \emph{Iter-130 closure path under Replacement (B).} The body of \texttt{cotangentSpaceAtIdentity} (post-iter-130 body swap) is \texttt{(ModuleCat.extendScalars $\psi_V$.hom).obj (ModuleCat.of $\Gamma(G, V)$ $\Omega[\Gamma(G, V)/\Gamma(\Spec k, U)]$)} for a chart $V$ around $\eta_G(\mathrm{pt})$. The rank lemma closes by combining \texttt{Algebra.IsStandardSmoothOfRelativeDimension.rank\_kaehlerDifferential} (Step 1 of the cross-check route above; gives rank $n$ over $\Gamma(G, V)$) with \texttt{Module.finrank\_baseChange} (\texttt{Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Dimension.Constructions}; gives $\texttt{Module.finrank}\ k\ (\texttt{TensorProduct}\ \Gamma(G, V)\ k\ \Omega[\ldots]) = \texttt{Module.finrank}\ \Gamma(G, V)\ \Omega[\ldots] = n$). Freeness over $k$ is supplied by \texttt{Algebra.TensorProduct.instFree} (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.TensorProduct.Free}). All four Mathlib names — \texttt{Algebra.IsStandardSmoothOfRelativeDimension.rank\_kaehlerDifferential}, \texttt{Module.finrank\_baseChange}, \texttt{Algebra.TensorProduct.instFree}, and \texttt{Algebra.IsStandardSmooth.free\_kaehlerDifferential} — are verified in Mathlib b80f227 by the iter-130 plan agent.
\end{proof}
